column5: Nice !!!!!!!! Good sign that so many hawgs are in the St Lawrance. Must mean the water quality is excellent.Thanks for sharing
the water is extremely clear tho...20 feet of water and we are watching the walleye while we are trolling over them!
awesome catch of eye's congrats
Hey Mike, I'll be right over!
HEY, YA WANA PICK ME UP ON THE WAY BY !!!
for supper?...im having fresh walleye...mmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmm
nice guy...... I'm having KD and tuna, ya wanna taste ???
i manufacture kd...lol...really

Buy more shares and crank up the production line, Mike. KD cooked al dente will become the next best selling flossing "bait". And you can take that to the bank. If you can get a line up with fluorescent colours, you'll get the kids' lunches AND the salmon and steelheader dudes.
bravo...
You have beautifull eyes !
??? Hmmmm
WOW! thoats awesome fishing boys!
Amazing!  There'll be a mass exodus of boats from Picton heading east this weekend.
nice bonus pickerel  where are the pike and muskie?
Hey Roy and Mercman, you have fish like that just minutes from your homes.......
SHSHHHH, we're creating a diversion.
...good idea...i meant to say that these beasts were from BOQ...st.lawrence doesnt have fish like this
St Lawerence ???? Roy and i live in Albuquerque New Mexico, near Shorty's Bar and Grill

me and my brother have been slautering giant walleye on the st.lawrence river this november  these pics are just the highlight of the past two days... all these fish are 7-9 pounds  we are averaging about 7 pounds and three to seven walleye a night with some bonus pike and musky

with pigs like this i dont think im gunna wast my time going to quinte ... a three hour drive...these fish are a mile from our dock!
we have pulled a 55 inch musky out of the same hole!
Very nice!!!!! HH
You don't need to go to Quinte when the big walleyes are there.  I remember going to Summerstown a decade or so ago, hoping for those fish, all we caught were pike  Excellent fish and report.
we are ver close to that area
Great catches man, look up photobucket. Much easier way to upload pictures and you can get them all on 1 post.  Thanks for sharing, MTBF
WOW nice fish! That'll rival BOQ anyday.
i dont have the pic but my brother got a 13 pounder a two weeks ago!
rather see the 55" than the bait.....
great fish  and now that people know, maybe it will take some pressure off BOQ walleye...LOL
it was in muskyhunter mag last year...he actually recaptured the same fish...first in the summer when she was thin then again in the fall when she was a lot fatter
probably not... we dont have the numbers to support 50 boats in a 5 km stretch
its no wonder I havent seen it  ....I take it you dont have the pictures to show then?
nope... i'll try to get em for ya
